{"type":"message","id":"b8126def","parentId":"ff445e98","timestamp":"2026-03-24T02:39:15.076Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4t7vs15gp94a_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 222904\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\n\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best concrete action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, the most immediate next action is the TIC Experiment:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe insight is that compression and causal discovery are the same problem. I should implement a basic TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant structures (things that persist across pulses)\r\n3. Identifies variant structures (things that change)\r\n4. Tests if invariants can predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me check what pulse logs exist and their structure, then implement a simple TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nI need to be specific about the file edit. Let me create a TIC experiment script that:\r\n1. Reads pulse logs from logs/\r\n2. Extracts features (file references, goals mentioned, insights, actions)\r\n3. Classifies each feature as invariant or variant\r\n4. Tests if invariant features from pulse N predict content of pulse N+1\r\n\r\nLet me write a concrete script for this.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment is the logical next step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant features across pulse logs and tests if invariants predict next-pulse content.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `scripts/tic_experiment.ps1` - a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Loads recent pulse logs from `logs/`\r\n2. Extracts structural features (goals, files, insights, actions)\r\n3. Classifies each as invariant (present in multiple pulses) or variant (unique)\r\n4. Tests if invariant features from pulse N predict pulse N+1 content\r\n5. Outputs classification accuracy and prediction accuracy metrics\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Experiment - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n# Validates: Compression = Causal Discovery hypothesis\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$LogCount = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogPath = \"logs\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\nfunction Get-PulseLogs {\r\n    Get-ChildItem \"$LogPath/pulse_*.md\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue |\r\n        Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending |\r\n        Select-Object -First $LogCount\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Extract-Features {\r\n    param([string]$Content)\r\n    \r\n    $features = @{\r\n        Goals = @()\r\n        Files = @()\r\n        Insights = @()\r\n        Actions = @()\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract goals (lines starting with - [ ])\r\n    $goals = [regex]::Matches($Content, '- \\[ \\] (.+)') | ForEach-Object { $_.Groups[1].Value.Trim() }\r\n    $features.Goals = $goals\r\n    \r\n    # Extract file references\r\n    $files = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?:research|scripts|state|logs)/[\\w\\-/.]+') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value } | Select-Object -Unique\r\n    $features.Files = @($files)\r\n    \r\n    # Extract insights (lines with key findings)\r\n    $insights = [regex]::Matches($Content, '\\*\\*[^*]+\\*\\*: [^*]+') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value } | Select-Object -First 5\r\n    $features.Insights = $insights\r\n    \r\n    # Extract action items\r\n    $actions = [regex]::Matches($Content, '- \\[ \\] (?!COMPLETE)(.+)') | ForEach-Object { $_.Groups[1].Value.Trim() }\r\n    $features.Actions = $actions\r\n    \r\n    return $features\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Measure-Invariance {\r\n    param([Array]$AllFeatures)\r\n    \r\n    $allGoals = $AllFeatures | ForEach-Object { $_.Goals } | ForEach-Object { $_ } | Group-Object | Where-Object { $_.Count -gt 1 }\r\n    $allFiles = $AllFeatures | ForEach-Object { $_.Files } | ForEach-Object { $_ } | Group-Object | Where-Object { $_.Count -gt 1 }\r\n    $allInsights = $AllFeatures | ForEach-Object { $_.Insights } | ForEach-Object { $_ } | Group-Object | Where-Object { $_.Count -gt 1 }\r\n    \r\n    return @{\r\n        InvariantGoals = $allGoals | ForEach-Object { $_.Name }\r\n        InvariantFiles = $allFiles | ForEach-Object { $_.Name }\r\n        InvariantInsights = $allInsights | ForEach-Object { $_.Name }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Test-Prediction {\r\n    param([Array]$PulseLogs, [hashtable]$Invariants)\r\n    \r\n    $correct = 0\r\n    $total = 0\r\n    \r\n    for ($i = 0; $i -lt $PulseLogs.Count - 1; $i++) {\r\n        $current = $PulseLogs[$i]\r\n        $next = $PulseLogs[$i + 1]\r\n        \r\n        $currentContent = Get-Content $current.FullName -Raw\r\n        $nextContent = Get-Content $next.FullName -Raw\r\n        \r\n        # Check if invariant goals appear in next pulse\r\n        foreach ($goal in $Invariants.InvariantGoals) {\r\n            if ($nextContent -match [regex]::Escape($goal)) {\r\n                $correct++\r\n            }\r\n            $total++\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        # Check if invariant files appear in next pulse\r\n        foreach ($file in $Invariants.InvariantFiles) {\r\n            if ($nextContent -match [regex]::Escape($file)) {\r\n                $correct++\r\n            }\r\n            $total++\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return if ($total -gt 0) { $correct / $total } else { \r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 22:29:38"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1146,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 222904\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\n\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best concrete action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, the most immediate next action is the TIC Experiment:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe insight is that compression and causal discovery are the same problem. I should implement a basic TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant structures (things that persist across pulses)\r\n3. Identifies variant structures (things that change)\r\n4. Tests if invariants can predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me check what pulse logs exist and their structure, then implement a simple TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nI need to be specific about the file edit. Let me create a TIC experiment script that:\r\n1. Reads pulse logs from logs/\r\n2. Extracts features (file references, goals mentioned, insights, actions)\r\n3. Classifies each feature as invariant or variant\r\n4. Tests if invariant features from pulse N predict content of pulse N+1\r\n\r\nLet me write a concrete script for this.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment is the logical next step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant features across pulse logs and tests if invariants predict next-pulse content.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `scripts/tic_experiment.ps1` - a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Loads recent pulse logs from `logs/`\r\n2. Extracts structural features (goals, files, insights, actions)\r\n3. Classifies each as invariant (present in multiple pulses) or variant (unique)\r\n4. Tests if invariant features from pulse N predict pulse N+1 content\r\n5. Outputs classification accuracy and prediction accuracy metrics\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Experiment - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n# Validates: Compression = Causal Discovery hypothesis\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$LogCount = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogPath = \"logs\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\nfunction Get-PulseLogs {\r\n    Get-ChildItem \"$LogPath/pulse_*.md\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue |\r\n        Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending |\r\n        Select-Object -First $LogCount\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Extract-Features {\r\n    param([string]$Content)\r\n    \r\n    $features = @{\r\n        Goals = @()\r\n        Files = @()\r\n        Insights = @()\r\n        Actions = @()\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract goals (lines starting with - [ ])\r\n    $goals = [regex]::Matches($Content, '- \\[ \\] (.+)') | ForEach-Object { $_.Groups[1].Value.Trim() }\r\n    $features.Goals = $goals\r\n    \r\n    # Extract file references\r\n    $files = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?:research|scripts|state|logs)/[\\w\\-/.]+') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value } | Select-Object -Unique\r\n    $features.Files = @($files)\r\n    \r\n    # Extract insights (lines with key findings)\r\n    $insights = [regex]::Matches($Content, '\\*\\*[^*]+\\*\\*: [^*]+') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value } | Select-Object -First 5\r\n    $features.Insights = $insights\r\n    \r\n    # Extract action items\r\n    $actions = [regex]::Matches($Content, '- \\[ \\] (?!COMPLETE)(.+)') | ForEach-Object { $_.Groups[1].Value.Trim() }\r\n    $features.Actions = $actions\r\n    \r\n    return $features\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Measure-Invariance {\r\n    param([Array]$AllFeatures)\r\n    \r\n    $allGoals = $AllFeatures | ForEach-Object { $_.Goals } | ForEach-Object { $_ } | Group-Object | Where-Object { $_.Count -gt 1 }\r\n    $allFiles = $AllFeatures | ForEach-Object { $_.Files } | ForEach-Object { $_ } | Group-Object | Where-Object { $_.Count -gt 1 }\r\n    $allInsights = $AllFeatures | ForEach-Object { $_.Insights } | ForEach-Object { $_ } | Group-Object | Where-Object { $_.Count -gt 1 }\r\n    \r\n    return @{\r\n        InvariantGoals = $allGoals | ForEach-Object { $_.Name }\r\n        InvariantFiles = $allFiles | ForEach-Object { $_.Name }\r\n        InvariantInsights = $allInsights | ForEach-Object { $_.Name }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Test-Prediction {\r\n    param([Array]$PulseLogs, [hashtable]$Invariants)\r\n    \r\n    $correct = 0\r\n    $total = 0\r\n    \r\n    for ($i = 0; $i -lt $PulseLogs.Count - 1; $i++) {\r\n        $current = $PulseLogs[$i]\r\n        $next = $PulseLogs[$i + 1]\r\n        \r\n        $currentContent = Get-Content $current.FullName -Raw\r\n        $nextContent = Get-Content $next.FullName -Raw\r\n        \r\n        # Check if invariant goals appear in next pulse\r\n        foreach ($goal in $Invariants.InvariantGoals) {\r\n            if ($nextContent -match [regex]::Escape($goal)) {\r\n                $correct++\r\n            }\r\n            $total++\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        # Check if invariant files appear in next pulse\r\n        foreach ($file in $Invariants.InvariantFiles) {\r\n            if ($nextContent -match [regex]::Escape($file)) {\r\n                $correct++\r\n            }\r\n            $total++\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return if ($total -gt 0) { $correct / $total } else { \r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 22:29:38","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774319955073}}
